Today, I put out my first folk EP in 10 years. It’s called My Birthday Again, a collection of the 5 singles I’ve released this year. As some of you may know, I made folk music from middle school through college. Then chronic pain forced me to stop playing guitar, so I started making pop music and working with producers. Then pain stopped me from singing too. When I could finally sing again, I stuck with pop, but I always felt like something was missing from my artistic life. I made the decision to go back to folk at the beginning of 2023 and I truly feel like I’m home again. Thank you all for taking this journey with me and I hope you like the music. Lots more to come soon ❤️

📸 by @benjybradshaw

New song out today! This one is close to my heart. I wrote it about one of my dad’s best friends, Michael Sample, a renowned wildlife photographer who was killed in 2014. Michael’s generosity enabled some pivotal parts of my life and this song serves to show the gratitude I never fully shared with him when he was alive.

I recorded this song in 2015 and I apologize if I’m forgetting anyone involved. Please comment if I am!

Co-production + Guitar by @danknobler 
Drums by @jburgerdrums 
Keys by @jakeshermanwooo 
Horns by members of @westerliesmusic 
Strings by @everydayimruslyn 
Backgrounds by @kiahvictoria and @johnfcardoza 
Mixed by @burritosinspace 
Mastered by @miketuccillo 
Artwork by @annavoloshyn

Got another new song for ya! “The Man I Planned” was written after visiting my sister and her kids, realizing that I didn’t really know how to interact with my nieces and nephew. I remembered being a kid and thinking how lame adults were, unable to play pretend or let loose like children can. I promised myself I wouldn’t lose those things, but it was clear in that moment that I had.

I hope this song resonates with you! Thanks to everyone who contributed:

Co-produced w @danknobler 
Background vocals by @johnfcardoza 
Mixing by @burritosinspace 
Mastering by @miketuccillo 
Artwork by @annavoloshyn

I moved my folk music over to Stefan Weiner on all platforms, with the pop still under Stefan Alexander and I’m slowly changing all my social media handles and my website. I’m also in the process of recording a new full length album of new music. 2024 is going to be a big year! Thanks for going on the journey with me ❤️

New single for your 👂s! It’s called “Smoke Alarm” and the lyrics were written in 2015 in the middle of 4 years of chronic pain that prevented me from singing or playing guitar. At the time, I felt like no matter what I did, no matter what decisions I made, I had no control over my life. Thankfully, I overcame my chronic pain, got back on stage and no longer feel that lack of agency, but this song will forever serve as a time capsule for that period in my life. I hope you like it ❤️

Special thanks to everyone who contributed to the song: @danknobler who co-produced the song with me many years ago, @burritosinspace who mixed the song, @miketuccillo my master mastering engineer, @jburgerdrums on drums / perc, @zubinhensler for electronic production and @kiahvictoria / @johnfcardoza who sang the heck out of the background vocals. The instrumental for this song was recorded so long ago that I know I’m leaving people off the list, but I appreciate you all so much for making this song a reality 💕
